The numbers are placed on a hexagonal spiral.  
For the hexagonal spiral the total number of cells up to ring \(k\) is  

\[
T(k)=1+3k(k+1).
\]

The number \(2026\) lies in ring  

\[
k=26\qquad\bigl(T(25)=1951<2026\le T(26)=2107\bigr).
\]

The first number of ring \(k\) is  

\[
S(k)=T(k-1)+1=2+3(k-1)k .
\]

Hence the first number of ring 26 is \(S(26)=1952\); the offset of 2026 in
that ring is  

\[
2026-1952 = 74 .
\]

Using axial coordinates \((q,r)\) with the directions  

\[
\begin{aligned}
\mathbf d_0 &=(-1,1),\quad
\mathbf d_1 =(-1,0),\quad
\mathbf d_2 =(0,-1),\\
\mathbf d_3 &=(1,-1),\quad
\mathbf d_4 =(1,0),\quad
\mathbf d_5 =(0,1),
\end{aligned}
\]

the cell \((26,0)\) is the start of the ring.  
Walking 74 steps gives the coordinate of 2026:

\[
(26,0)\xrightarrow{\mathbf d_0\,26}
(0,26)\xrightarrow{\mathbf d_1\,26}
(-26,26)\xrightarrow{\mathbf d_2\,22}
(-26,4).
\]

Thus \(2026\) is at \((-26,4)\).
Its six neighbours are obtained by adding the six direction vectors:

\[
\begin{aligned}
(-27,5),\; (-27,4),\; (-26,3),\; (-25,3),\; (-25,4),\; (-26,5).
\end{aligned}
\]

For a coordinate \((q,r)\) let \(s=-q-r\); the ring of the cell is
\(k=\max\{|q|,|r|,|s|\}\).
The number belonging to a cell is the start of its ring plus the offset
obtained by walking from \((k,0)\) along the directions \(\mathbf d_i\).

Carrying this out gives the neighbour numbers

\[
\begin{array}{c|c}
\text{coordinate} & \text{value}\\ \hline
(-27,5) & 2184\\
(-27,4) & 2185\\
(-26,3) & 2027\\
(-25,3) & 1874\\
(-25,4) & 1873\\
(-26,5) & 2025
\end{array}
\]

Finally, their sum is

\[
2184+2185+2027+1874+1873+2025 = \boxed{12168}.
\]
